	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 18th 6:01 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Also check out www.EQdruids.com.<br><br>Yes, all druids get forage, but in my experience, I tried to focus on that and still only got my skill up to an 8. There is a certain amount of real time that you are down between being able to forage. Quite a few minutes (15?).<br><br>It goes like this:<br>Forage - nothing<br>wait 15 min.<br>Forage - nothing<br>wait 15 min.<br>Forage - grapes<br>Etc.<br><br>Now I have summon water and summon food spells and don't even bother with foraging. In my experience, foraging shouldn't be a determining factor.<br><br>Please see my "RE: Whats the best class for a Druid??" message for my view on the benefits of the hiding skill (halfling only).<br><br>As for points, I followed the advice of a few of the sites and put a ton of points into WIS to get myself up to a 110 starting stat. Then the rest I think I put 2 or 3 in STR or AGI, I forget, but WIS is definitly the most important.<br><br>STR for carying (also melee, but after around level 20 you won't be meleeing much).<br><br>AGI for quickness and dodging blows. I figured this one would be important because even if I wasn't doing melee, I knew creatures would be.<br><br>STA for longevity and hit points. I find we have enough STA buff spells that this doesn't need to be touched.<br><br>CHA for charms and spell resists. Kind of important, but I left this one alone too. I can pick up a +15 CHA necklase and wear it occasionally if need be.<br><br>WIS equals Mana, the druids live blood. For every point of WIS you have, you get a certain amount of Mana. You can NEVER have too much WIS or too much Mana. In early levels +Mana items are good, but later on they are outweighed by the benefits of +WIS items.<br><br>INT for learning and skill increases. I don't thik I bumped this one up either and have noticed no discernable bad efects. I level fine and my skills go up pretty regularly.<br><br>DEX for better chance to hit an opponent. Again, not important in the long run for melee, but I think I read somewhere that higher DEX helps you recover from blows that might interupt your casting. Again, the snare spell slows down my opponents just fine for me to cast all but the longest duration spells.<br><br>Uh...I think that about covers it. Hope it helps.<br>And remember, this is just my opinion, don't forget to go out and research for yourself. =)<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Webee Jammin<br>Halfling Druid of Prexus<br>Flower Jihad<br>---please rate my post---</td></tr>
